Pattern: Read-only system namespaces in Subcog

When adding system-managed content that users shouldn't modify:
1. Add variant to Namespace enum (e.g., Namespace::Help)
2. Implement is_system() method returning true for system namespaces
3. Implement user_namespaces() to exclude system namespaces from user enumeration
4. Add ReadOnlyNamespace error variant to CaptureError
5. Check is_system() in CaptureService.capture() to reject writes
6. Apply weight adjustment in RecallService to deprioritize system content (0.7x)

This pattern ensures:
- Users can search/recall system content
- Users cannot overwrite or pollute system content
- System content doesn't dominate user memory search results
- Clear separation between user and system namespaces